                "protocols": [
                    {
                        "comments": [],
                        "name": "Sample collection",
                        "protocolType": {
                            "comments": [],
                            "annotationValue": "Sample collection",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>Seeds of Arabidopsis thaliana wild type (Col-0) and 'bglu23-1 bglu21-1' mutant were surface sterilized by 70% (v/v) ethanol, washed with absolute ethanol, and then dried with a vacuum. Seeds were sown in an area (1 cm^2) on vermiculite covered with nylon mesh sheet. Seedlings were germinated at 22 \u00b0C under 18 h light/6 h dark for 7 days. Aerial parts of seedlings were harvested and then homogenized with liquid nitrogen. The seedling homogenates were analyzed before and after incubation at 26 \u02daC for 30 min to allow any \u03b2-glucosidases present to react with their substrates.</p>",
                        "uri": "",
                        "version": "",
                        "parameters": [
                            {
                                "comments": [],
                                "parameterName": {
                                    "comments": [],
                                    "annotationValue": "",
                                    "termSource": null,
                                    "termAccession": ""
                                }
                            }
                        ],
                        "components": []
                    },
                    {
                        "comments": [],
                        "name": "Extraction",
                        "protocolType": {
                            "comments": [],
                            "annotationValue": "Extraction",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>The experiment was outsourced to Kazusa DNA Research Institute (LC-MS Basic Analysis, <a href='http://www.biosupport.kazusa.or.jp/sub_center3/index.php/lcms-basic/' rel='noopener noreferrer' target='_blank'>http://www.biosupport.kazusa.or.jp/sub_center3/index.php/lcms-basic/</a>).</p><p><br></p><p>Briefly, between 100-150 mg of sample was place in 2 ml plastic tubes. An extraction solution [0.1% (v/v) formic acid and 80% (v/v) MeOH] of 500 \u00b5l to 100 mg of sample was added. After a zirconium bead was added, metabolites were extracted using a TissueLyser (25 freq, 2 min) followed by sonification (2 min). Debris was spun down by 15000 rpm for 10 min at 4 \u00b0C, and then filtered. Next was spin column conditioning with the following conditions: i) 100 \u00b5l MeOH, 5000 x g for 2 min at 4 \u00b0C; ii) 100 \u00b5l water, 5000 x g for 2 min at 4 \u00b0C; and iii) 200 \u00b5l extraction solution, 5000 x g for 2 min at 4 \u00b0C. The resultant extract was filtered theough a PTEE membrane (pore size 0.2 \u00b5m). The samples were diluted x 10 or x 100 with extraction solution (subjected as 'lipid removed' samples).</p>",
                        "uri": "",
                        "version": "",
                        "parameters": [
                            {
                                "comments": [],
                                "parameterName": {
                                    "comments": [],
                                    "annotationValue": "Post Extraction",
                                    "termSource": null,
                                    "termAccession": ""
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "comments": [],
